Step 1: Stop Jenkins

On the old server:

sudo systemctl stop jenkins

This prevents file changes during backup.

Step 2: Backup Jenkins Home

Jenkins stores almost everything in:

/var/lib/jenkins

Create backup:

sudo tar -czvf jenkins-backup.tar.gz /var/lib/jenkins

Verify:

ls -lh jenkins-backup.tar.gz
Step 3: Upload Backup to S3

Configure AWS CLI:

aws configure

Upload:

aws s3 cp jenkins-backup.tar.gz s3://my-jenkins-backup/

Verify:

aws s3 ls s3://my-jenkins-backup/
Step 4: Launch New EC2

Create a new EC2 instance.

Install:

Java
Jenkins
Git

Example:

sudo dnf install java-21-amazon-corretto -y

Install Jenkins.

Do not configure it yet.

Stop Jenkins:

sudo systemctl stop jenkins
Step 5: Download Backup from S3
aws s3 cp \
s3://my-jenkins-backup/jenkins-backup.tar.gz .
Step 6: Restore Jenkins Home

Remove current Jenkins data:

sudo rm -rf /var/lib/jenkins/\*

Restore:

sudo tar -xzvf jenkins-backup.tar.gz -C /

You should get:

/var/lib/jenkins

restored.

Step 7: Fix Permissions
sudo chown -R jenkins:jenkins /var/lib/jenkins
Step 8: Start Jenkins
sudo systemctl start jenkins

Verify:

sudo systemctl status jenkins
