Interview Answer

Jenkins data is stored in /var/lib/jenkins. To migrate Jenkins to a new EC2 instance, I stop Jenkins, create a compressed backup of the Jenkins home directory, upload it to an S3 bucket using AWS CLI, launch a new EC2 instance, install Jenkins, download the backup from S3, restore it to /var/lib/jenkins, fix ownership permissions, and start Jenkins. For production environments, I prefer EBS snapshots or automated S3 backups for disaster recovery and migration.
